A hashbang (also called a shebang) is the first line in a script file that tells the system which interpreter to use when executing the script from the command line.

For PHP, the hashbang looks like this:

#!/usr/bin/env php

steps to make console file to treat as php file :
Open the file in VS Code.

    Press Ctrl+Shift+P (or Cmd+Shift+P on Mac) to open the Command Palette.

    Type and select: Change Language Mode.

    Type or select: PHP.

    üîÅ This is temporary ‚Äî it lasts until you close the file.
